---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="Machine Tending — Formic"
  description="Mill, lathe, and injection-mold tending — Formic recovers spindle uptime without adding shift coverage."
  ogTitle="Machine Tending — Formic"
  ogDescription="Mill / lathe / mold tending under Formic Full Service. Recover spindle time without staffing it."
>
  <link rel="canonical" href="https://formic.co/solutions/machine-tending" slot="head" />

<div class="detail-bc">
  <a href="/">Home</a><span class="sep">/</span><a href="/solutions">Solutions</a><span class="sep">/</span>Machine Tending
</div>

<section class="detail-hero">
  <div class="si">
    <div class="slabel" style="color:var(--orange)">Machine Tending</div>
    <h1>Mill, lathe, mold —<br><em>hands-off.</em></h1>
    <p class="lede">Robotic load/unload for the most repetitive, dangerous, and hardest-to-staff jobs on a precision manufacturing floor — automated under the Formic Full Service model.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-block dark">
  <div class="detail-video wide">
    <div class="detail-video-frame">
      <video autoplay muted loop playsinline poster="/MachineTending-CNC.jpg">
        <source src="/Formic-Header.mp4" type="video/mp4" />
      </video>
      <span class="dv-fpo">FPO</span>
      <span class="dv-cap">CNC tending · lights-out cycle</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-block white">
  <div class="db-grid">
    <div class="db-text">
      <div class="db-tag">01 — Why It Matters</div>
      <h2>Spindle uptime is <em>everything</em>.</h2>
      <p>In precision manufacturing, a stopped spindle is lost margin. Most shops are losing 20–40% of available spindle time to operator-bound load/unload cycles, breaks, and shift changes. Robotic tending recovers that time without adding shift coverage.</p>
      <ul class="feats">
        <li>Lights-out third shift on existing equipment</li>
        <li>Operator focus shifts from load/unload to multi-machine supervision</li>
        <li>Consistent cycle-to-cycle quality, no shift drift</li>
      </ul>
      <a href="/#cta" class="larr">Scope my shop →</a>
    </div>
    <div class="db-img"><img src="/MachineTending-CNC.jpg" alt="Robot tending a CNC machine" loading="lazy"/><span class="img-cap">CNC mill · 24/7 spindle</span></div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-block lgrey">
  <div class="db-grid flip">
    <div class="db-img">
      <video autoplay muted loop playsinline poster="/MachineTending-CNC.jpg">
        <source src="/ATLAS_EOAT.webm" type="video/webm" />
      </video>
      <span class="img-cap">Vision pick · part presentation</span>
    </div>
    <div class="db-text">
      <div class="db-tag">02 — How It Works</div>
      <h2>Vision pick, <em>repeatable place</em>.</h2>
      <p>Bin or fixture-based part presentation. Vision-guided pick handles part orientation. Robot loads, machine cycles, robot unloads. Out-of-spec parts get diverted at the gauge before they ever leave the cell.</p>
      <ul class="feats">
        <li>Compatible with most major CNC, lathe, EDM, and injection mold platforms</li>
        <li>Inline gauging integration for in-cell quality verification</li>
        <li>Bin picking from gaylords, totes, or fixtured trays</li>
        <li>Multi-machine tending — one robot, two or three spindles</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-block white">
  <div class="db-grid">
    <div class="db-text">
      <div class="db-tag">03 — Specs</div>
      <h2>Built for <em>your machines</em>.</h2>
      <p>Designed to integrate with the spindles you already run. We adapt around the machine, not the other way around.</p>
      <ul class="feats">
        <li>Reach: 1.3 – 2.6 m, with track-extended options for multi-machine cells</li>
        <li>Payloads: 5 – 150 kg, EOAT-dependent</li>
        <li>Compatible with most major CNC, lathe, EDM, and IMM platforms</li>
        <li>Cycle integration: M-code, Modbus, EtherNet/IP, OPC UA</li>
        <li>Safety: scanners, fenced or collaborative configurations available</li>
      </ul>
      <a href="/#cta" class="larr">Talk to engineering →</a>
    </div>
    <div class="db-img"><img src="/Talos-9787.jpg" alt="Robot loading a precision part into a fixture" loading="lazy"/><span class="img-cap">Fixtured load · gauge · unload</span></div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-block dgrey">
  <div class="detail-video wide">
    <div class="detail-video-frame">
      <video autoplay muted loop playsinline poster="/Talos-9787.jpg">
        <source src="/Formic-Header.mp4" type="video/mp4" />
      </video>
      <span class="dv-fpo">FPO</span>
      <span class="dv-cap">Multi-machine tending · single cell</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-cta">
  <h2>Recover the spindle hours<br><em>you're already paying for.</em></h2>
  <div class="btn-row">
    <a href="mailto:sales@formic.co" class="btn-ctadark">Get Started</a>
    <a href="/solutions" class="btn-ctawh">All Solutions</a>
  </div>
</section>
</Layout>
